text: I know this was just a coincidence ,but it still creeps me out. I never really got into Stephen king books ,I have 3,the shining ,doctor sleep ,IT...I got IT today ,the same day I got the DVD for Annabelle comes home. I start the movie and all the trailers that show before the movie starts ,all 3 of the trailers for the movies/books by Stephen king played. I was just talking about Stephen king and then  realized doctor sleep was on. If any of you know who Phil Lester's is ,well he posted a picture of Annabelle in the case on his story because he went to the place where they keep her blah blah blah. I paused the movie while it was showing Annabelle ,checked my Instagram for a bit and then there was Annabella again...I kinda started to freak out because I have a glass doll name bella ,I now can't find her anywhere in my room ,nor where we keep my other glass dolls... so now I am stuck finishing the movie by myself with a missing glass doll name bella! text: As a HUGE fan of this universe since The Conjuring came out in 2013, it pains me to say this, but I was majorly disappointed with this movie. I think it was an ingenious concept to give us insight on the objects in that room which we have been curious about for years, but I think that the end result was very disappointing. There was SOO much emphases on 5 objects(the board game, the TV, the ferryman, the wedding dress, and the Hellhound) that we've only seen on screen for maybe a total of one second combined  leading up to this movie and therefore has harbored no curiousity whatsoever. Yet pillar objects such as the Samurai and the Monkey, who we've seen every. single. time. the camera is in that room were completely disregarded and done a MAJOR injustice. Even when the girls were reading through the case files, every one they read was one of the aforementioned 5 objects. We still don't know anything about the Samurai, who is a major focal point of the room. Not what he does, how he does it, where he came from, or even how he got a spot in the Warren room. The events that took place in the hall tell us that he was most likely in a war of some sort but that's not a shocking detail as he is literally a Samurai. Another detail of the movie that I cant shake, is how much time is spent in movie on absolute nonsense. We would get 20 minutes of dialogue for maybe 2 minutes worth of actual, important information. Im not talking about the Warren's giving details of them leaving or the school scene (which is very important). I'm talking about the 10 minutes in a car which old told us that Annabelle was a beacon to other spirits (which we already knew), the entire grocery store scene was a complete waste of time, and although some might disagree, I felt that the scene in the  Chicken coop and the entire backstory of the Friend of the Babysitter was time wasted. We have never even heard about this girl and for her to be plopped in as a main character in the movie out of nowhere just feels sloppy and not well thought out. Which is mind boggling to me considering the intricate web of stories and lives that intermingle and connect one movie to another. I know that based of this one movie there is potential for countless other movies in the future but i feel that more work and effort could have been made on this one. This movie is/was the most anticipated horror movie in 2019 and it was a waste of money and time.
author: Magnolia Rose

text: It really bothers me to hear some people accusing Ed and Lorraine of being frauds, con artists, fakes, etc. THEY WERE *NOT* frauds! They were legitimate, experienced, professional demonologists and agents of the Catholic Church, who had the highest regards for The Warrens and their work. They both valued their integrity and credibility with their career. Ed was the only non-ordained Demonologist recognized by The Vatican and Lorraine was a very gifted clairvoyant.       Like I said, they NEVER charged any money for their services they provided for 60+ years. So how is that fraudulent? They were both equally passionate about what they did, they traveled around the world helping people in paranormal distress, bring peace back into family households, and educated thousands on the paranormal.       My friend was a personal friend of Lorraine and he said she was nothing less than A SAINT. She was the most loving, compassionate, caring, genuine, kind, selfless, empathetic, wonderful woman heâ€™d ever met, and he witnessed her clairvoyance in action. She was an extraordinary woman who never went anywhere without Ed, and Ed never went anywhere without Lorraine. They were true soulmates and their skilled and passionate abilities in the supernatural brought them together. They touched the lives of countless people and were genuinely GOOD PEOPLE.       It really irks and bothers me when people accuse them of being â€œfraudsâ€ because that canâ€™t be farthest from the truth. Thereâ€™s definitely frauds in the world, but Ed and Lorraine were *NOT* one of them. They were legitimate, courageous professionals who used the light and love of God to banish out darkness and evil.

text: A couple of tips to survive or avoid being in a horror movie:   1. DON'T MOVE!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! 2. If you ignore the first rule then DON'T MOVE TO THE MIDDLE OF NOWHERE WITH NO NEIGHBOURS!!!! 3. Again if you ignore my first two rules the DON"T MOVE TO A HOUSE WITH A HISTORY OF SUSPICIOUS MURDERS. Matter of fact DON'T MOVE TO A HOUSE WITH ANY MURDERS. 4. DON'T MOVE TO HOUSE WITH A BASEMENT OR ATTIC. 5. Don't go to a cabin, ESPECIALLY A CABIN IN THE WOODS. 6. Stay away from DOLLS!!!! 7. Usually can't be helped but don't be an orphan, maybe? 8. Don't watch tapes that might kill you. EASILY AVOIDABLE. 9. If you find yourself already in a horror movie. DON'T TAKE SHOWERS, DON'T TAKE BATHS! Figure it out. 10. Stay away from Nuns. I don't know why they are such a danger, they just are.   Bonus tip, 'cause I'm so nice. When you realise what is happening, GET TF OUT!!!!!! That should go without saying. Also, listen to your damn kids when they tell you what is going on.   Also, NEVER GO BACK, to anywhere, EVER

text: Lorraine Warren has just passed away on April 18th, 2019. As a long-term fan of both her and Ed, I am devastated. They were a wonderful couple who passionately and courageously conducted more than 10,000+ cases all over the world. They never charged a single penny and selflessly helped people out of the goodness of their hearts. Iâ€™m sad that theyâ€™re both gone now, but at least theyâ€™re together again â¤ï¸ğŸ™ğŸ»  *EDIT: Whoever says Lorraine and Ed were frauds are being very ignorant. THEY WERE NOT frauds! They were legitimate, experienced, and professional demonologists and agents of the Catholic Church, who had the highest regards for The Warrens and their work. Ed was the only non-ordained Demonologist and Lorraine was a very gifted clairvoyant. Like I said, they NEVER charged any money for their services that they provided for 60+ years. So how is that fraudulent? They were both equally passionate about what they did, they traveled around the world helping people in paranormal distress, bring peace back into family households, and educated thousands on the paranormal. My friend was a personal friend of Lorraine and he said she was nothing less than A SAINT. She was the most loving, compassionate, caring, genuine, kind, selfless, empathetic, wonderful woman heâ€™d ever met, and he witnessed her clairvoyance in action. She was an extraordinary woman who never went anywhere without Ed, and Ed never went anywhere without Lorraine. They were true soulmates and their skilled and passionate abilities in the supernatural brought them together. They touched the lives of countless people and were genuinely GOOD PEOPLE. It really irks and bothers me when people accuse them of being â€œfraudsâ€ because that canâ€™t be farthest from the truth. Thereâ€™s definitely frauds in the world, but Ed and Lorraine were **_NOT_** one of them. They were legitimate, courageous professionals who used the light and love of God to banish out the darkness and evil of demons.*

text: While this might be a fun film to watch with friends, I fear it won't be an actual good film, because big Hollywood films are scared to make horror films and not use jumpscares. Jumpscares are a really "safe" route, as they bring out a physical reaction in the audience. Take that last shot in this trailer for instance: When she lifts up her blanket, and Annabelle is under there, I got a bit of chills, but then remembered "Oh yeah, this is a Hollywood film, so we'll get a jumpscare in 3, 2, 1..." and it came. If they had just KEPT the shot there on Annabelle under the blanket, and kept us audience there long after, it would have been so much more effective in my book. With that jumpscare, the whole tension of that creepy shot was ruined.

text: I HAVE TO SAY I LOVED THE CONJURING 1 AND 2 (AND CAN'T WAIT FOR PART 3) BUT I NEVER HAD ANY INTEREST IN THE SPIN-OFFS THEY DID (ANNABELLE, THE NUN) BUT AS SOON AS I SAW ED AND LORRAINE WERE IN IT (AND THEIR DAUGHTET JUDY) I KNEW I HAVE TO SEE IT!!!! AGAIN THEY WEREN'T IN THE SPIN-OFFS  AND THE STORY LINES WE NOT REAL) BUT THIS.... IS LIKE A TEASE TILL THE CONJURING 3 COMES OUT.... AS LONG AS THESE MOVIE'S HAVE THE WARRENS IN IT THEN I WILL CONTINUE TO WATCH AND LOVE THEM..... THEY DID SUCH A GREAT JOB WHEN THEY CASTED VERA AS LORRAINE AND PATRICK AS ED.... I ALWAYS SAID WHY DON'T THEY MAKE HORROR MOVIES BASED ON REAL CASES WITH THE WARRENS AND THEY FINALLY DID... I WILL SAY THE CONJURING IS ONE OF THE BEST HORROR MOVIES EVER MADE (ESPECIALLY IN THE LAST 30 YEARS).... KEEP IT UP... JUST DON'T LIKE THE FACT JAMES WAN ISN'T DIRECTING PART 3 OR THIS... ANYWAY I'M SUPER EXCITED ABOUT THIS AND IT CAME AS A SURPRISE I CAN'T BELIEVE I DIDN'T HEAR OR READ ABOUT THIS..... I VISITED THE REAL/ACTUAL MUSEUM BECAUSE THE WARRENS LIVE IN CT (WELL LORRAINE, SINCE WE PASSSED AWAY). TONY SPEARA TOOK OVER GREAT GUY ANYWAY IT WAS REAL DOPE OF COURSE THE REAL MUSEUM DOESN'T LOOK LIKE THE ONE IN THE MOVIE... IT WAS COOL THOUGH... I HEARD PART 3 WILL BE BASED ON A WEREWOLF CASE, WHICH I'M NOT TRILLED ABOUT WISH THEY KEEP IT IN THE PARANORMAL WORLD MAYBE EVEN DO THE SNECKER CASE IN SOUTHINGTON, CT.... THAT WAS A CRAZY CASE THEY WORKED ON.....

text: Warner Brothers, you don't have to remind everyone that these movies follow the same continuity. You don't have to shove in the word "universe" your audience is smarter than that. Take Transformers (80s cartoon) it was connected to Jem, GI Joe, Battle Beast AND Visionaries but the beauty was that we found that out in little hints and "easter eggs" and it wasn't shoved down our throats. So try to bringing it back a bit on the whole "universe" thing...also, using the term universe with these movies really doesn't fit well. Something old world like, Lore, or "Tales of", etc. sounds way better. Universe is too sci-fi sounding for this franchise.
